Since the end of the 1960s in East Africa, no leader has shaken up a country in peacetime, and the region, in five years like Magufuli did.One has to go back to the very opposite spectrum, to military dictator Field Marshal Idi Amin in Uganda, to find something close. Tanzania’s fifth president, John Pombe Magufuli, will be buried in his Chato hometown, in Geita region, northwestern Tanzania, today. Dr Magufuli was more than a handful, and there will be a lot of more personal things to say about his rule in the times ahead.  



