We’ll remember Pombe for a long time. 

Mr Onyango-Obbo is a journalist, writer and curator of the Wall of Great Africans. @cobbo3 African regimes have a history of reserving the most extreme, and bizarre, treatments for journalists. The ban on Ugandan and Tanzanian maize was, ostensibly, because there has been an increase in aflatoxin-related illnesses in Kenya. Incident leaves fruit vendor with tattered clothes and nursing injuries. No patient is hooked to a ventilator while only eight are on oxygen support. Driver who was reversing a Toyota pickup truck belonging to the company is said to have run over the tree in 2017.